astor Jon Tyson from Church of the City in New York City joins us to preach on the important topic of prayer. He offers a framework that challenges us to grow in our prayer lives as we pursue a compelling vision of prayerful surrender.','Prayer - Jon Tyson','','publish','closed','closed','','prayer-jon-tyson','','','2020-08-25 19:01:38','2020-08-25 19:01:38','',0,'http://icondevsite.wpengine.com/?post_type=sermons&#038;p=283',0,'sermons','',0),(284,2,'2019-09-09 18:41:31','2019-09-09 18:41:31','','Part 1 - Christianity Gives Life Meaning','','publish','closed','closed','','part-1-christianity-gives-life-meaning','','','2020-08-25 19:01:07','2020-08-25 19:01:07','',0,'http://icondevsite.wpengine.com/?post_type=sermons&#038;p=284',0,'sermons','',0),(285,2,'2019-09-16 18:43:40','2019-09-16 18:43:40','','Part 2 - Christianity and Science','','publish','closed','closed','','part-2-christianity-and-science','','','2020-08-25 19:01:14','2020-08-25 19:01:14','',0,'http://icondevsite.wpengine.com/?post_type=sermons&#038;p=285',0,'sermons','',0),(286,2,'2020-01-13 18:50:49','2020-01-13 18:50:49','This week kicked off our official Gospel of John series, \'Witness to the Light.\' Pastor Justin preached from John 20:30-31, which serves as a thesis statement for the entire book. In it, John says that he wrote his gospel so that people would believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God and that by believing people would have life in his name. This is the frame through which John sees the life of Jesus and retells his story. For more information, go to iconchurch.org.','John 20:30-31 – Witness to the Light','','publish','closed','closed','','john-2030-31-witness-to-the-light','','','2020-08-25 19:00:00','2020-08-25 19:00:00','',0,'http://icondevsite.wpengine.com/?post_type=sermons&#038;p=286',0,'sermons','',0),(287,2,'2020-01-20 18:51:53','2020-01-20 18:51:53','Week 2 of our John series takes us back to chapter 1 and a reintroduction of John the Baptist. Emissaries of the Pharisees question John, asking him, \"who are you?\" This simple question is the existential one that all of us have to answer. See how John\'s answer doesn\'t only tell us who he is but can help us answer that question for ourselves. For more information, go to iconchurch.org.','John 1:19-34 – Witness to the Light','','publish','closed','closed','','john-119-34-witness-to-the-light','','','2020-08-25 19:06:31','2020-08-25 19:06:31','',0,'http://icondevsite.wpengine.com/?post_type=sermons&#038;p=287',0,'sermons','',0),(288,2,'2019-12-02 18:55:18','2019-12-02 18:55:18','Our Advent series kicked off this week by looking at the theme of Hope from John 1:1-5. Pastor Justin challenged the congregation to consider what it is they hope for and what do they depend on to bring about that hope. John 1 teaches us that life in Christ is our greatest hope and that Jesus, the Light for the world is the only means by which we can realize that truest hope.','Hope','','publish','closed','closed','','hope','','','2020-08-24 22:22:54','2020-08-24 22:22:54','',0,'http://icondevsite.wpengine.com/?post_type=sermons&#038;p=288',0,'sermons','',0),(289,2,'2019-12-09 18:56:21','2019-12-09 18:56:21','Week 2 of our advent series was about the kind of Peace that can come from knowing who you are and what you were made for. John the Baptist served as a great example of someone who was secure in who he was and what God had sent him to do, which meant that he wasn\'t striving for something more. He wasn\'t trying to control the future or reaching for more control. He was confident and content to be who God made him to be.','Peace','','publish','closed','closed','','peace','','','2020-08-25 21:41:49','2020-08-25 21:41:49','',0,'http://icondevsite.wpengine.com/?post_type=sermons&#038;p=289',0,'sermons','',0),(290,2,'2020-08-24 19:14:12','2020-08-24 19:14:12','','Chae','','inherit','open','closed','','chae-4','','','2020-08-24 19:14:12','2020-08-24 19:14:12','',0,'http://icondevsite.wpengine.com/wp-conte